definitions: designed or represented in a non-realistic way using artistic conventions or simplified forms
examples: The logo features a stylized eagle in gold
Artists created stylized portraits using geometric shapes

definitions: having a sophisticated charm and smooth confidence in manner and appearance
examples: The suave diplomat handled negotiations with charm
His suave manner impressed everyone at the party

definitions: relating to regions immediately south of the Arctic Circle with cold climates
examples: Subarctic forests support unique wildlife species
The subarctic climate brings long, harsh winters

definitions: existing at a scale smaller than atoms or relating to particles within atoms
examples: Scientists study subatomic particles in accelerators
Quantum mechanics describes subatomic behavior patterns

definitions: situated or applied under the skin in the layer between skin and muscle
examples: The medication requires subcutaneous injection daily
Subcutaneous fat provides insulation for the body

definitions: quiet and lacking in intensity, often deliberately restrained in manner
brought under control by force or persuasion after resistance
examples: The restaurant had subdued lighting and music
She spoke in subdued tones during the meeting
The rebels were finally subdued after months
Police subdued the violent protestor without injury

definitions: based on personal feelings, tastes, or opinions rather than external facts
examples: Art criticism is often subjective and personal
Pain levels are subjective experiences for patients

definitions: brought under domination or control, especially by conquest or force
examples: The subjugated peoples fought for their freedom
Colonial powers subjugated indigenous populations for centuries

definitions: of such excellence, grandeur, or beauty as to inspire great admiration or awe
examples: The mountain views were absolutely sublime
Her sublime voice moved the audience to tears

definitions: below the threshold of conscious perception but able to influence mind and behavior
examples: Advertisers sometimes use subliminal messages in commercials
The subliminal sounds affected test subjects' moods

definitions: existing, occurring, or used under the surface of the sea
examples: Submarine cables carry internet data across oceans
The submarine volcano erupted beneath the waves

definitions: completely covered or hidden beneath the surface of water or another liquid
examples: The submerged rocks posed danger to boats
Ancient ruins lay submerged beneath the lake

definitions: designed to operate while submerged under water for extended periods
examples: The submersible pump works efficiently underwater
Scientists use submersible vehicles for ocean exploration

definitions: ready to conform to the authority or will of others without resistance
examples: The dog became submissive around larger animals
Her submissive behavior worried her concerned friends

definitions: lower in rank or position within a hierarchy or organization
examples: She manages several subordinate team members daily
The subordinate clause depends on the main clause

definitions: having arranged to receive something regularly by paying in advance
examples: All subscribed members receive monthly newsletter updates
The subscribed users have access to premium content

definitions: written or printed below and to the side of another character
examples: Chemical formulas use subscript numbers for atoms
The subscript notation indicates the array index

definitions: prepared to obey others unquestioningly, often in an excessive or servile way
examples: His subservient attitude annoyed his independent colleagues
The subservient role of women changed over time

definitions: serving to assist or supplement something of greater importance or size
examples: The company operates several subsidiary businesses overseas
Subsidiary evidence supported the main legal argument

definitions: supported financially by paying part of the costs from public or organizational funds
examples: The subsidised housing helps low-income families afford homes
Students enjoy subsidised meals in the cafeteria

definitions: supported financially by paying part of the costs from public or organizational funds
examples: The government offers subsidized healthcare for seniors
Farmers receive subsidized loans during drought years

definitions: relating to or flying at speeds less than the speed of sound
examples: Most commercial aircraft fly at subsonic speeds
The subsonic wind tunnel tests airplane designs

definitions: below the usual or required standard of quality, size, or performance
examples: The substandard construction led to building collapse
Workers complained about substandard safety equipment provided

definitions: having a firm basis in reality and therefore important, meaningful, or considerable
examples: The report contained substantive policy recommendations
We need substantive changes, not cosmetic ones

definitions: acting or serving in place of someone or something else
examples: The substitute teacher handled the class well
We used substitute ingredients when originals ran out

definitions: existing or occurring below the surface of something, especially the ground
examples: Subsurface water flows through underground channels
Engineers detected subsurface cracks in the foundation

definitions: existing, occurring, or done under the earth's surface in underground spaces
examples: The city has extensive subterranean tunnel systems
Subterranean creatures adapted to life without light

definitions: relating to or involving the removal or subtraction of material, color, or quantity
examples: Sculpture uses subtractive methods like carving marble
The subtractive color model combines cyan, magenta, yellow

definitions: relating to regions adjacent to or bordering the tropics with warm climates
examples: Florida has a humid subtropical climate year-round
Subtropical plants thrive in warm, moist conditions

definitions: seeking or intended to undermine the power and authority of established systems
examples: The government banned subversive political literature
Her subversive art challenged traditional social norms

definitions: coming after something in time or order as the next item
accomplishing an aim or purpose with positive results
examples: Each succeeding generation builds on previous knowledge
The succeeding chapters explain advanced concepts
The succeeding business strategies increased profits significantly
Students kept succeeding despite difficult circumstances

definitions: following one another or following others in uninterrupted sequence or order
examples: The team won three successive championship titles
Successive waves crashed against the rocky shore

definitions: briefly and clearly expressed using few words without unnecessary detail
examples: Please provide a succinct summary of findings
Her succinct response answered all our questions

definitions: tender, juicy, and tasty, especially describing food items
having thick, fleshy tissues adapted to store water
examples: The chef served succulent grilled chicken breasts
We enjoyed succulent peaches fresh from the orchard
Desert gardens feature various succulent plant species
Succulent leaves help plants survive dry conditions

definitions: making it difficult or impossible to breathe, either literally or figuratively oppressive
examples: The smoke created a suffocating atmosphere inside
She felt trapped in a suffocating relationship

definitions: containing a lot of sugar or having an excessively sweet taste
examples: Children often prefer sugary breakfast cereals
The sugary drink left a sticky residue

definitions: tending to suggest an idea or meaning indirectly, often with sexual implications
examples: His suggestive comments made everyone uncomfortable
The painting contains suggestive imagery and symbolism

definitions: having or showing a desire to kill oneself due to mental distress
so dangerous or reckless as to be likely to cause death
examples: The counselor helped patients with suicidal thoughts

definitions: right or appropriate for a particular person, purpose, or situation
examples: Please wear suitable clothing for hiking
This book is suitable for young readers

definitions: right or appropriate for someone or something's needs, character, or circumstances
examples: They seem perfectly suited for each other

definitions: relating to or containing sulfur, especially in its highest valence state
examples: Battery acid contains concentrated sulfuric acid solution

definitions: bad-tempered and sulky, showing irritation through gloomy silence
examples: The teenager gave a sullen response

definitions: relating to or containing sulphur, especially in its highest valence state
examples: The laboratory stored dilute sulphuric acid safely
Sulphuric compounds create acid rain problems

definitions: hot and humid weather that feels oppressive and uncomfortable
attractive in a way that suggests passionate sexual desire
examples: The sultry summer evening made everyone restless

She gave him a sultry look across the room

definitions: extremely costly, rich, luxurious, or magnificent in appearance or quality
examples: Guests enjoyed a sumptuous feast at the palace
The hotel suite had sumptuous silk furnishings

definitions: of various kinds forming a collection of different items
examples: The drawer contained sundry office supplies
She collected sundry items for the garage sale

definitions: having gone down below the surface of water or ground
deeply affected by or absorbed in a particular state
examples: The ship has sunk to the ocean floor

definitions: having sunk or been submerged below the normal or surrounding level
examples: The sunken garden created a peaceful retreat

definitions: illuminated by direct light from the sun creating brightness
examples: We ate breakfast in the sunlit kitchen
